Cinnamon-Swirl Brioche French Toast

Brioche Base
• 1 large loaf day-old brioche (about 500 g)
• Slice 3.5–4 cm thick

⸻

Cinnamon Roll Swirl Paste
• 6 tbsp unsalted butter, very soft, divided
• ½ cup packed brown sugar
• 1½ tsp ground cinnamon
• ¼ tsp fine sea salt
• 1 tsp vanilla extract

Method — Swirl
Melt 2 tbsp of the butter gently. Stir in the cinnamon and allow to bloom for 30 seconds off heat. Combine with remaining butter, brown sugar, salt, and vanilla. Mix until smooth and homogeneous.

Using a small offset spatula, spread a thin spiral on one cut face of each brioche slice, stopping 1 cm from the edge. Lay parchment over the surface and gently press to level. Chill 20 minutes to firm the swirl and prevent bleed during soaking.

⸻

Mascarpone Custard Soak
• 1 cup (250 g) mascarpone, room temperature
• 3 large eggs
• ¾ cup (180 ml) 35% whipping cream
• ½ cup (120 ml) whole milk
• ¼ cup maple syrup (Grade A, amber or dark)
• 1 tbsp granulated sugar
• 1 tsp vanilla extract
• ¼ tsp fine sea salt

Method — Custard
Whisk mascarpone until completely smooth and elastic. In a separate bowl, whisk eggs, maple syrup, sugar, and vanilla just until combined, avoiding aeration. Whisk in cream and milk.

Gradually incorporate the liquid mixture into the mascarpone in stages until fully emulsified and silky. Add salt last, then strain through a fine sieve or chinois. Rest refrigerated 20 minutes.

⸻

Soaking
Stand brioche slices upright in a shallow dish. Pour custard around the slices, not directly over the tops, allowing slow capillary absorption. Soak 3–4 minutes per side. The slices should feel heavy and saturated but remain structurally intact.

⸻

Cooking
Heat a heavy skillet or cast-iron pan over medium-low. Add a 50/50 mix of unsalted butter and neutral oil. When butter foaming subsides, place slices swirl-side down. Cook 3–4 minutes until deeply golden and aromatic. Flip carefully and cook another 3 minutes. Adjust heat downward as needed to avoid scorching sugar and dairy.

⸻

Optional Oven Finish
For very thick slices or service volume, transfer to a 180 °C oven for 5–7 minutes until the interior is custard-set: soft, creamy, and without liquid flow.

⸻

Optional Restaurant Garnish (Minimal, Controlled)
• Warm maple syrup (light application)
• Icing sugar, very light dust
• Toasted pecans or hazelnuts
• Fine orange or lemon zest
